&lt;p&gt;Thought I&apos;d just add that the answer given by Dr.Flink can also be applied to a Bootstrap 3 &lt;code&gt;form-horizontal&lt;/code&gt; block - which can be very handy if you want to use background colours for each cell. In order for this to work for bootstrap forms, you would need to wrap the form contents which just serves to replicate a table-like structure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The example below also provides the CSS which demonstrates an additional media query allows Bootstrap 3 to simply takeover and do it&apos;s normal thing on the smaller screen(s). This also works in IE8+ .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;pre class=&quot;default s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-xml&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-name&quot;&gt;form&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt;=&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;form-horizontal&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;role&lt;/span&gt;=&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;form&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-name&quot;&gt;div&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt;=&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;form-wrapper&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
